description:
&lt;p&gt;Applications are invited to apply for a general Haematology post from&lt;br /&gt;dynamic individuals. The vacancy has arisen due to the retirement of&lt;br /&gt;one of the Consultants. The new post holder will join a team of three&lt;br /&gt;other Consultant Haematologists.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;The post requires the candidate to have a good grounding in general&lt;br /&gt;and malignant Haematology and contribute to inpatient and outpatient&lt;br /&gt;Haematology, including out-of-hours Haematology on call.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;At Wirral University Teaching Hospital, the candidates will join a team of&lt;br /&gt;three other full time Consultant Haematologists, one Specialist Registrar,&lt;br /&gt;two CMT Doctors, a Haematology Advanced Nurse Practitioner, 1.8 whole&lt;br /&gt;time equivalent Clinical Nurse Specialists and 2.0 whole time equivalent&lt;br /&gt;Haematology Specialist Nurses. Wirral University Teaching Hospital forms&lt;br /&gt;part of the Cheshire and Merseyside cancer network and is recognised as&lt;br /&gt;a BCSH level 2B service.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt;For further details or informal visits contact Dr. Barbara Hammer,&lt;br /&gt;Clinical Lead for Haematology on 0151 678 5111 or email&lt;br /&gt;barbarahammer@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Previous applicants need not apply&lt;/p&gt;
